  "prompt": "How do I hand wash my converse shoes?",
  "response": "Here's a step-by-step guide to hand washing Converse shoes:\n\n1. Remove laces\n\u2022 Take out the shoelaces to wash separately\n\u2022 This allows you to clean the entire shoe more thoroughly\n\n2. Prepare cleaning solution\n\u2022 Mix warm water with a small amount of mild detergent or laundry soap\n\u2022 Avoid harsh chemicals or bleach\n\n3. Scrub the shoes\n\u2022 Use a soft brush or old toothbrush\n\u2022 Gently scrub the canvas and rubber parts\n\u2022 Pay extra attention to dirty or stained areas\n\n4. Clean the soles\n\u2022 Use the brush to remove dirt and debris from the rubber soles\n\u2022 Wipe with a damp cloth if needed\n\n5. Rinse thoroughly\n\u2022 Use clean, cool water to rinse off all soap\n\u2022 Make sure no soap residue remains\n\n6. Dry the shoes\n\u2022 Stuff shoes with paper towels to absorb moisture and maintain shape\n\u2022 Air dry at room temperature\n\u2022 Avoid direct sunlight or heat sources\n\u2022 Let them dry completely before wearing\n\n7. Optional: Clean laces\n\u2022 Wash laces separately in the same soap solution\n\u2022 Rinse and let air dry\n\nTips: Don't machine wash or put in dryer, as this can damage the shoes.",
